b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Linear is best suited for engineering teams, startups, product teams, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Monday.com AI, meanwhile, shines for marketing teams, operations, mid size companies, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, Linear describes itself as \"Streamlined issue tracking tool built for high-performance software teams.\" Monday.com AI, established in 2012, positions itself as \"Work OS with AI-powered automation, project tracking, and team collaboration.\" With 7 years between them, Monday.com AI brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Linear offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Linear** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 8.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Monday.com AI is a poor choice — far from it. Monday.com AI excels in its own right, particularly for marketing teams and operations.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value fastest issue tracker available, go with Linear. If beautiful and intuitive board interface matters more to you, Monday.com AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
